X
\left \{ 1,2,3,4,5,6,\ldots \right \}
\mathbb{E}[X]=\sum_{i=1}^\infty \mathbb{P}[X \ge i]
\rm\bf Note
\rm\bf Rhetorical\text{ } question
\mathrm{P}(X=n)
n=1,2,3,\dots
\sum_{k=1}^\infty\; \mathrm{P}(X\ge k)=\sum_{k=1}^\infty\; \sum_{\ell=k}^\infty\; \mathrm{P}(X=\ell)
